Hey guys,
Earlier today, my code wasn’t running properly because the spark max versions weren’t up to date with the robo rio. So I plugged the laptop into the can bus through the power distribution panel while the robot was on and I updated the sparks through the REV Hardware Client like I normally do. However, the update process wasn’t working properly, and after it wasn’t making any progress for 20 minutes I restarted the app and power cycled the robot. But after the powering the robot back on, the status lights on the all the spark max motor controllers in the can bus were dark and wouldn’t turn on even after I powered cycled the robot multiple times. My computer stopped recognizing the spark max as devices as well when I tried connecting to them directly using USB C, suggesting there was some malfunction with the spark max itself. I’ve never encountered this issue before and I’m not exactly sure what to do; Could the sparks have been corrupted because the firmware update didn’t finish? Are they dead?
Any help would be greatly appreciated,
Thank you!

Hello!

My team had nearly the same issue last year, and we found that all of our sparks had been put into “recovery mode”. You can find details on documentation online, but generally you should take a small point (i.e. sowing needle) and press the red button that’s across from the status light. While holding, plug in with usb-c and hardware client open. Then release the button, and it should show!
